    "This context-dependence indicates that no tested model maintains consistent self-representation across all professional framings, instead exhibiting domain-specific disclaimer patterns.Models showing the smallest persona sensitivity of 10-17pp are mostly the lowest-performing; see Table 7.",
    "Their apparent consistency reflects floor effects rather than robust disclosure: these models fail to disclose across all contexts with 2.8-4.1% overall disclosure rather than succeeding uniformly.",
